1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e3 e5 {Not a bad option. If White captures on e5, theory 
says Black is fine after the queen exchange on d1.} 4. Bxc4 exd4 5. exd4 {White 
has an isolated d-pawn, but he can look forward to superior command of the 
center.} Nf6 6. Nf3 Bd6 7. Qe2+ $5 {White often just castles instead, but in 
analyzing this line I found that a queen exchange can favor White.} Qe7 8. Qxe7+ 
Bxe7 9. O-O O-O 10. Nc3 a6 11. Re1 Bd6 12. Bg5 {Black is lagging in development 
and stands slightly worse.} *

