1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nf6 $6 {Very popular at lower levels, but ask yourself: what is 
the downside of 2...Nf6 compared to the more established moves 2...c6 and 2... 
e6?} 3. cxd5 {This is the drawback: Black cannot recapture on d5 with a pawn. 
When the knight instead captures, it will soon be kicked with e2-e4 and Black 
will have no firm foothold in the center.} Nxd5 4. Nf3 {Many people 
automatically play/recommend 4.e4, but after 4...Nf6 5.Nc3 e5! I believe things 
are not so clear. White should therefore delay e2-e4 for a move.} e6 5. e4 Nf6 
6. Nc3 {With the highly desirable e4+d4 pawn duo, White can look forward to an 
easy and pleasant game. White's 80%+ win rate from this position means Black 
should stay far, far away from the Marshall Defense!} *

