1. d4 d5 2. c4 e5 3. dxe5 {The Albin Counter-Gambit is best accepted, of 
course.} d4 {Black gains some space with this move and will subsequently look to 
recover the e5-pawn.} 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. a3 {Covering b4, but more importantly 
preparing b2-b4-b5.} Nge7 {5...Bg4 is best met by 6.Nbd2.} 6. b4 {Instead of 
defending e5, White is menacing b4-b5 and planning to win Black's d4-pawn.} Ng6 
7. Bb2 a5 {Or 7...Ngxe5 8.Nxe5 Nxe5 9.e3.} 8. b5 Ncxe5 9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. e3 Be6 
11. Bxd4 Nxc4 12. Qc2 Nd6 13. Nc3 {Black has managed to equalize the material, 
but White has an easier game. For the moment Black has some trouble completing 
kingside development because of the attack on g7} ({13...Be7? 14.Bxg7 Rg8 
15.Qxh7}) {.} *

