1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 c5 {Striking the undefended d-pawn.} 5. 
dxc5 {In the 4.Qc2 Nimzo White's best bet is usually to play dxc5 when 
prompted.} O-O 6. a3 Bxc5 7. Nf3 {A common error would be 7.Bg5? Bxf2+! 8.Kxf2 
Ng4+, picking up the bishop on g5.} b6 8. Bf4 {Given Black's weaknesses on d6 
and c7, I think this is the proper place for White's bishop.} Bb7 9. Rd1 
{x-raying Black's queen.} Nc6 10. e3 {White may next play Bf1-e2 and 0-0.} *

