1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 {Another pawn stab at White's center!} 
5. cxd5 exd5 {Black can also play 5...Qxd5 (the Romanishin System), upon which I 
usually answer 6.Nf3.} 6. Bg5 h6 7. Bxf6 {If you'd prefer a greater risk/ reward 
ratio, 7.Bh4 is your move. After (for instance) 7...c5 8.dxc5 the game will 
plunge in to complications!} Qxf6 8. a3 Bxc3+ 9. Qxc3 O-O 10. e3 c6 11. Nf3 
{White scores a bit better from this position. A minority attack (b2-b4-b5) may 
eventually be feasible on the queenside.} *

