1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 Nc6 {A solid line that was recommended by 
IM Christof Sielecki in his book 'Opening Repertoire: Nimzo and Bogo Indian'.} 
5. Nf3 d6 6. Bd2 {It's a decent idea for White to preface a2-a3 with this move 
so as to enable Bd2xc3.} O-O 7. a3 Bxc3 8. Bxc3 Qe7 9. e3 e5 10. d5 Nb8 11. Nd2 
{White is ready to play Bf1-d3 and castle short.} *

