1. d4 d5 2. c4 Bf5 {You'll face this once in a blue moon. Memorize the following 
line and you'll be fine!} 3. cxd5 Bxb1 {If 3...Qxd5, then Black is clearly worse 
after 4.Nc3 followed (ideally) with 5.e4. Hence, Black hurries to eliminate the 
knight.} 4. Qa4+ {An intermezzo that disrupts Black's coordination.} c6 5. Rxb1 
Qxd5 6. Nf3 Nd7 7. b4 Ngf6 8. e3 e6 9. Qc2 {With the bishop pair and an extra 
central pawn White can be pleased with the result of the opening.} *

